section.section:
The following public service companies shall pay a tax on their operating property to the state, and to the extent the operating property is subject to local taxation, shall pay a local tax to the county, incorporated city, and taxing district where its operating property is located:
Railway companies;
Sleeping car companies;
Chair car companies;
Dining car companies;
Gas companies;
Water companies;
Bridge companies;
Street railway companies;
Interurban electric railroad companies;
Express companies;
Electric light companies;
Electric power companies, including wind turbine and solar generating companies;
Commercial air carriers;
Air freight carriers;
Pipeline companies;
Privately owned regulated sewer companies;
Municipal solid waste disposal facilities, as defined by KRS 224.1-010(15), where solid waste is disposed by landfilling;
Railroad car line companies, which means any company, other than a railroad company, which owns, uses, furnishes, leases, rents, or operates to, from, through, in, or across this state or any part thereof, any kind of railroad car including, but not limited to, flat, tank, refrigerator, passenger, or similar type car; and
Every other like company or business performing any public service.

The following companies shall not be subject to the provisions of paragraph (a) of this subsection:
Bus line companies;
Regular and irregular route common carrier trucking companies;
Taxicab companies;
Providers of communications service as defined in KRS 136.602;
Providers of multichannel video programming services as defined in KRS 136.602; and
A qualified air freight forwarder as defined in KRS 141.121.
